  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Business Administrator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>REDOX CHEMICAL PTE LTD, incorporated in Singapore in 1993, specializes in the manufacturing of cleaning, maintenance and specialty chemicals for the marine and offshore industries. We have been accredited with ISO 9001 certification by Bureau Veritas (UK) since 1999 and went on to achieve ISO 14001 certification by the same certifying body in 2002. We have also successfully achieved OSHA 18000 and BizSAFE Star Standard for our factories recently.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Manage and optimize quality and compliance processes including ISO documentation and audits, inventory accuracy, licensing, and supplier coordination to support operational excellence and regulatory adherence.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead the implementation, maintenance, and audit coordination of ISO documentation to ensure compliance with quality management standards</li><li>Conduct inventory management and stock taking with precision to maintain accurate and up-to-date records supporting operational efficiency</li><li>Monitor licensing, regulatory compliance, and permit renewals to ensure uninterrupted business operations and adherence to legal requirements</li><li>Execute purchasing activities by sourcing suppliers, processing purchase requests, and coordinating with vendors to secure timely and cost-effective procurement</li><li>Support management by performing additional ad hoc duties that contribute to team and organizational objectives</li></ul>",
